notes.content: A trombone and case, including the mouthpiece, innerslide, and outerslide. The trombone is a Stradivarius Model 36 made by the Vincent Bach Corporation. There is a serial number at the bottom on the cylinder where all the tubes converge: [28892].

notes.label: Description
notes.content: This sheet music is for the song "Good Night Angeline" composed by James Reese Europe, Noble Sissle, and Eubie Blake. It was published by M. Witmark & Sons. The cover has blue and black printed text accompanied by illustrations in blue of a snare drum and a flugelhorn surrounding a black-and-white portrait of Europe. The portrait is below a black-and-white photograph of the 369th Infantry Regimental Band. The interior pages contain the music and lyrics printed in black and white. The back cover has an advertisement for the publisher with the first page of the sheet music for the song "Kiss Me Again" by Henry Blossom and Victor Herbert.

notes.label: Description
notes.content: Sheet music for the song “General La Fayette Bugle Waltz” composed by Francis Johnson. The sheet music is printed on off white paper in black ink. Text at the top of the sheet music reads “No. 7 of Taw’s Musical Miscellany – Copy right secured / GENERAL LA. FAYETTE BUGLE / WALTZ / Composed by / F. JOHNSON / Philadelphia Published for the Author.” The sheet music has handwritten numbers written in graphite above some of the ledger lines. There are no marks or inscriptions on the verso.
